# for-each [![build status][1]][2]

A better forEach.

## Example

Like `Array.prototype.forEach` but works on objects

``` js
var forEach = require("for-each")

forEach({ key: "value" }, function (value, key) {
    /* code */
})
```

## Installation

`npm install for-each`
